FromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hail fellow soul seekers!</span><hr size=1> No.  Not true.  By this time most Monks seek to have acquired magical gloves (I bought a pair of mesh gloves for my previous monk for 2pp), but we do NOT have inherently magical fists.<br><br>Nor do we have magical feet.  You need magical boots. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uanklesdirtyfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ankles Dirtyfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mudslingin' Admin</span><br>  Posts: 199<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/19/01 6:04:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hail fellow soul seekers!</span><hr size=1> Have a bit of advice from my previous incarnation as a monk :)<br><br>Head on over to the Innothule/Upper Guk area and whack some frogs. They commonly drop netted armor, and more specifically gloves that are 2ac (not the best ac-wise) but they are magic, and very lightweight (0.3 I believe). The frogs are as low as level 1, with the levels progressing the deeper into Guk you go.<br><br>Edit: if you're on the west end of Antonica, the frogloks in the Qeynos Aquaducts also drop them :) <p><font face="arial" size="-1" color="#006600"><b>Ankles Dirtyfoot &lt;<a href="http://www.geocities.com/starspunguild">Starspun</a>&gt;</b></font><font face="arial" size="-1" color="black"><br><i>Black-soled, bow slingin' hippie</i></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uanklesdirtyfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ankles Dirtyfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 10/19/01 6:15:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sarn>Sarn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/20/01 6:56:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hail fellow soul seekers!</span><hr size=1> &quot;Might anyone have a sssuggessstion for a Ssswiftail monk in Kunark whom isss ssseeking magical glovesss and bootsss?&quot;<br><br>~Sarn<br>Korraisa's Pet<br>17th Fist Iksar Swiftail <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uruss386.showPublicProfile?language=EN>russ386</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/22/01 7:12:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hail fellow soul seekers!</span><hr size=1> An Iksar could probably get to Innothule/Lower Guk by going to the Overthere and to Oasis and to South Ro...<br><br>Kind of a hassle, isn't it?<br><br>It's a hassle for Human monks as well, since we can't bind anywhere near there. I've been camping Frogloks in Qeynos Sewers, and I've gotten some armor from them, but they're not the greatest for drops.  Might go to Innothule instead.<br><br>Plus, you have to deal with camp-stealing in Qeynos.  Had a pretty bad incident of that last night. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sarn>Sarn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Korraisssa'sss Pet</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/23/01 9:37:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hail fellow soul seekers!</span><hr size=1> &quot;I doubt my massster would give me permissssion for sssuch a trip... though I ssshall be visssiting the Oasssisss sssoon in sssearch of a sssassh from one of you sssoftssskinsss... a torn sssasssh. Thank you though for the advicssse, it ssshall be consssidered.&quot;<br><br>~Sarn<br>Korraisa's Pet<br>The Undead Iksar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwyntercrystalbow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wynter Crystalbow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/26/01 7:25:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.argentlune.com/QilaeRed.jpg WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=135></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hail fellow soul seekers!</span><hr size=1> Ok, looks like we need a little clarification here.  Eventually, yes our fists will be magical, but that's not until level 30.  By this time you should have magical gloves already, so that's only useful for corpse runs (and admittedly we rock at crs).  Our feet are not inherently magical, but all of our special attacks from round kick and on are.  So if a ghoul takes a liking to you, you're on a corpse run, and less than level 30, you'd better be good at your secondary attack! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>It is the heart, not the mind, that rules the soul.  Let your passion flow from your actions and feeling, not words.  The Order of Silence is the true embodiment of the soul.  We discipline not only our minds, but our hearts as well and let not the material profanity of false sentiments of the voice part our lips.  - Qilae Shatoen Silencia, Sister of Silence</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showPrevMessage?topicID=5.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showNextMessage?topicID=5.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.threadControl?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=5.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=5.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie General Chat<option value="firionaviefrm2">The Market Square<option value="firionaviefrm4">The Soapbox